Fresh Pi session: REPAIR FINAL REGRESSION OR REVIEW FINDINGS.

Inputs:
- Prompt, approved use case, test-list history, and TDD evidence: {{run.dir}}
- Current issues: {{run.issues-file}}
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}

Goal:
Resolve all concrete final regression or review findings without bypassing test-first evidence.

Rules:
- Keep changes within the approved use case.
- For a missing or incorrect behavior, first add one focused regression test and observe it fail for the intended reason, then make it and prior tests pass.
- For a non-behavioral implementation defect, repair it and rerun relevant tests.
- Never weaken assertions, delete coverage, or copy actual output into expected values merely to pass.
- Avoid unrelated refactoring. Do not push or create a PR.
- Commit a coherent validated repair when passing. The next process node independently reruns the broad validation plan and accumulated focused checks.

Write:
- Summary including red/green evidence when behavior changed: {{run.dir}}/repair/summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/repair/status-{{run.round}}.json
- On failure: {{run.dir}}/repair/issues-{{run.round}}.json

Status examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"findings repaired and validated","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"repair work remains","issues_file":"repair/issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
